Poland to Halt 862 Megawatts of Power Capacity This Weekend

-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-03-24T14:30:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/poland-to-halt-862-megawatts-of-power-capacity-this-weekend-1-.html
Power companies in  Poland  will halt
862 megawatts of generating capacity during this weekend for
maintenance, grid operator  PSE Operator SA  said.  PGE SA will stop a 261-megawatt unit at the Elektrownia
Turow plant from 12:01 a.m. on March 26 for 72 hours, the
operator said today in a statement. A 386-megawatt unit at PGEâ€™s
Elektrownia Opole will be halted from 7:01 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. on
March 26.  Electricite de France SA will shut a 215-megawatt unit at
Elektrownia Rybnik from 12:01 a.m. on March 26 for 24 hours.  To contact the reporter on this story:
